race.description: Tab Federal Tony Campbell Memorial Cup Hcp (Bm60)
race.comment: HOLY HELL (11) made a winning return at Moruya, arriving just in time to score fresh off a long break. She failed to fire second-up at Bathurst when well supported, but with 37 days between runs she looks ready to bounce back. From a tricky draw she'll need luck but a strong tempo will play into her hands. STORMBRINGER (7) resumed with authority and was only nailed late when chasing back-to-back wins last time. Drawn to advantage third-up, he should give another bold sight on speed. RILEYCAT (12) improved nicely second-up, digging deep to score narrowly at Goulburn. With further improvement expected and a soft draw, she looks set to be charging late again. NEESON (9) broke through impressively at Corowa, justifying his short price. This is tougher, but he maps well and can continue progressing. XCEPTIONAL FELLA (4) returned with a barnstorming win here in a strong form race. With natural improvement, he's right among the winning hopes.
